<Project Sdk="Microsoft.NET.Sdk">

  <PropertyGroup>
    <TargetFramework>netstandard2.0</TargetFramework>
    <Company />
    <Product>ConfigTextFile</Product>
    <Authors>Michael McBride</Authors>
    <RepositoryUrl>https://github.com/Michmcb/ConfigTextFile</RepositoryUrl>
    <RepositoryType>Github</RepositoryType>
    <PackageTags>config text fluent</PackageTags>
    <PackageProjectUrl>https://github.com/Michmcb/ConfigTextFile</PackageProjectUrl>
    <Description>A .NET library which allows you to read and write plain-text configuration files</Description>
    <PackageLicenseFile>LICENSE</PackageLicenseFile>
    <PackageReleaseNotes>- Added some convenience methods to IConfigElements
- Trying to set the Value of an ArrayConfigElement or SectionConfigElement now throws an InvalidOperationException (as they don't have values). Getting the value of these still returns an empty string
- ConfigInvalidElement now throws ConfigInvalidElementException in certain cases. It also can have its Value set/get, to provide for value indicating invalid (such as empty string or null)
- ConfigFileReader and ConfigFileWriter have been added, for low-level reading/writing of ConfigTextFiles.
- FluentConfigFileWriter has also been added. Its syntax ensures you will write a valid file and it's less verbose to use than the ConfigFileReader.</PackageReleaseNotes>
    <PackageIcon>icon.png</PackageIcon>
    <Version>1.3.0</Version>
    <PackageRequireLicenseAcceptance>true</PackageRequireLicenseAcceptance>
    <AssemblyVersion>1.3.0.0</AssemblyVersion>
    <FileVersion>1.3.0.0</FileVersion>
  </PropertyGroup>

  <ItemGroup>
    <None Include="..\..\LICENSE">
      <Pack>True</Pack>
      <PackagePath></PackagePath>
    </None>
    <None Include="..\icon.png">
      <Pack>True</Pack>
      <PackagePath></PackagePath>
    </None>
  </ItemGroup>

  <ItemGroup>
    <PackageReference Include="Microsoft.Extensions.Configuration" Version="3.1.4" />
    <PackageReference Include="Microsoft.Extensions.Configuration.Abstractions" Version="3.1.4" />
  </ItemGroup>

</Project>
